question.title: <nulltype> cannot be represented as a Class<?> SDK 35 in Android
question.body:
I was using compile 34 as the target SDK in my project and it gave me a warning that I should now make it 35. So I made the compile SDK 35 and then when I did the rebuild it gave me an error like this. The error text is very long I had no problems running on android 34. There are some sections about room in the error message. But I don't know if I updated the room and gson versions before the error.

Android Studio Ladybug | 2024.2.1 Patch 3

android {
    useLibrary 'org.apache.http.legacy'
    compileSdk 35
    defaultConfig {
        applicationId "com.myapp"
        minSdkVersion 23
        targetSdk 35
        targetSdkVersion 35

The content of the error is as follows
